Rothbart (ECBQ)

“In the last two weeks”

1. “When approached by an unfamiliar person in a public space (for example., the grocery store), how often did your child cling to a parent?”

2. “While having trouble completing a task (e.g.building, drawing, dressing), how often did your child get easily irritated?”

3. “When a familiar child came to your home, how often did your child seek out the company of the child?”

4. “When offered a choice of activities, how often did your child decide what to do very quickly and go for it?”

5. “During daily or evening quiet time with you and your child, how often did your child enjoy just being quietly sung to?”

6. “While playing outdoors, how often did your child choose to take chances for the fun and excitement of it?”

7. “While engaged in play with his/her favorite toy, how often did your child play for more than 10 minutes?”

8. “While engaged in play with his/her favorite toy, how often did your child continue to play while at the same time responding to your remarks or questions?”

9. “When told that loved adults would visit, how often did your child get very excited?”

10. “During quiet activities, such as reading a story, how often did your child fiddle with his/her hair, clothing, etc.?”

11. “While playing indoors, how often did your child like rough and rowdy games?”

12. “When being gently rocked or hugged, how often did your child seem eager to get away?”

13. “When encountering a new activity, how often did your child get involved immediately?”

14. “When engaged in an activity requiring attention, such as building with blocks, how often did your child tire of the activity relatively quickly?”

15. “During everyday activities, how often did your child pay attention to you right away when you called to him/her?”

16. “During everyday activities, how often did your child seem to be irritated by tags in his/her clothes?”

17. “During everyday activities, how often did your child become bothered by sound while in a noisy environment?”

18. “During everyday activities, how often did your child seem full of energy, even in the evening?”

19. “While in a public place, how often did your child seem afraid or large, noisy vehicles?”

20. When playing outdoors with other children, how often did your child seem to be one of the most active children?

21. “When told”no, how often did your child stop the forbidden activity?

22. “When told”no, how often did your child become sadly tearful?

23. “Following an exciting activity or event, how often did your child seem to feel down or blue?”

24. “When playing indoors, how often did your child run through the house?”

25. “Before an exciting event (such as receiving a new toy), how often did your child get very excited about getting it?”

26. “When he/she asked for something and you said”no, how often did your child have a temper tantrum?

27. “When asked to wait for a desirable item (such as ice cream), how often did your child wait patiently?”

28. “When being gently rocked, how often did your child smile?”

29. “While being held on your lap, how often did your child mold to your body?”

30. “When a familiar adult, such as a relative or a friend, visited your home, how often did your child want to interact with the adult?”
